:: 1. Freeze requirements
pip freeze > requirements.txt

:: 2. Initialize Git and Upload
:: REPLACE THIS URL
set "REPO_URL=https://github.com/YourUsername/YourRepo.git"

git init
git remote add origin %REPO_URL%
git add .
git commit -m "Final project upload"
git push -u origin master

:: 3. Verify status
git status

:: 4. STOP: Check your GitHub repo in the browser to ensure files are there!

:: 5. Teardown (Delete Local Project)
:: Deactivate venv first to unlock files
deactivate

:: Move up one level
cd ..

:: Delete the folder and everything in it
rmdir /s /q "%PROJECT_NAME%"
echo Local project deleted.
